wikipedia_page.main: Ronald Stuart Jakeman (20 September 1943 – 24 December 2013) was an English cricketer active from 1959 to 1966 who played for Northamptonshire (Northants).He was born in Holmfirth, the son of Freddie Jakeman. He appeared in three first-class matches as a lefthanded batsman who scored 31 runs with a highest score of 20. He died in 2013

response: He also appeared for an England XI in 1951, the Rest of England in 1952, for Yorkshire Second XI from 1946 to 1948, for a Scotland XI in 1945 and the Minor Counties in 1948.  His son, Stuart Jakeman, played three games for Northants in 1962 and 1963.
